FLY CARBON FIBER INTAKE VENT WING/BREATH GUARD

catalog_description:
You've seen Fly Racing's elite athlete's such as Colten Moore and Heath Frisby dominate the winter games taking home multiple medals.  Racer's such as Tucker Hibbert, Ross Martin, and factory Yamaha taking snocross and cross country podiums and championships.  Backcountry experts Dan Adams and Geoff Kyle, hillclimbers like Russ Frisby, Erin Beukelman, the Sharp family, Tapio brothers, and many more, all dominating the snow wearing our F2 helmet.  Fly Racing now introduces our snow specific F2 Carbon helmet.

  • Snell M2010, DOT approved for USA.  Other safety standards include ECE and AS (Australian).  Meets or exceeds the toughest safety standards on the market.
  • ISR approved for any type of snowmobile competition
  • Visible snow specific graphic and design
  • Same shell and interior feautres as the current F2 Carbon helmet
  • Includes a cold weather plug kit to help block the cold weather
  • Features a custom molded F2 breath deflector to block flying debris

catalog_description:
NEW SHELL DESIGN:

  • Modern Styling
  • Large eyeport that accepts large goggles
  • Roomier jaw area for increased comfort
  • Eyeport trim has integrated “Roost Deflector"
  • Larger bottom opening that allows for increased comfort when putting on and removing the helmet
  • Two shell sizes with three styro sizes for comfort fitting

DOT APPROVED: 

  • Lightweight thermo-plastic poly alloy shell

VENTING - INDUSTRY LEADING 17 VENTS: 

  • Maximum air flow is achieved thru shell/Styro and comfort liner vents

NEW LATERAL STYRO INSERTS:

  • These additional support inserts are located between the cheek pads and the shell
  • Increased comfort and outside sound reduction

PLUSH REMOVABLE WASHABLE INTERIOR:

  • Removable washable check pads.Different sizes available for purchase to obtain a custom fit
  • Integrated speaker pockets in cheek pads will except most communication devices

REMOVABLE CHEEK PADS:

  • New design for comfort and reduction of outside noise
  • Allows for custom fitting with optional sized cheek pads
  • Washable

NEWLY DESIGNED MOUTH PIECE/VENT:

  • High flow venting
  • Allows for quick and easy removal from the front of the helmet
  • Removable and washable foam dust filter

groups.51800: FLY F2 CARBON ANDREW SHORT REPLICA HELMETS
FLY F2 CARBON ANDREW SHORT REPLICA HELMETS
FLY F2 CARBON ANDREW SHORT REPLICA HELMETS

description: F2 CARBON SHORTY HELMET BLACK/YELLOW/BLUE L
catalog_description:
The F2 Carbon represents race-inspired lightweight helmet technology for the masses. Based on the same platform as the Formula MX, the F2 Carbon shares many of the technological features as its predecessor, yet still carves out its own unique FLY Racing style and identity.

  • SNELL, DOT APPROVED FOR USA - other standards include: ECE and AS (Australian). Meets or exceeds the toughest safety standards on the market
  • COMPOSITE CONSTRUCTION SHELL – outer shell is constructed using state-of-the-art, aircraft grade woven carbon fiber and Kevlar® composite materials, which creates superior strength while remaining extremely light
  • DUAL DENSITY EPS LINER – two layers of EPS (Expanded Polystyrene), one softer one slightly harder, combine to provide more progressive impact absorption for different levels of impact
  • MULTI-PORT AIR INDUCTION COOLING SYSTEM – eleven (11) intake and four (4) exhaust vents create massive airflow to keep your head cool
  • TRI-VENT GOGGLE ANTI-FOG VENTS – three (3) air intake vents above goggle eye port draw air from goggle to help clear away fog
  • CUSTOM MOLDED RUBBER TRIM WITH NOSE GUARD - with its smooth lines the integrated nose guard helps keep pesky rocks away from your nose
  • QUICK RELEASE WASHABLE COMFORT LINER & CHEEK PADS – plush liner absorbs sweat, provides plenty of ventilation, and is easy to remove and clean with out “Quick Snap” system
  • FLOW THROUGH EPS AND COMFORT LINER AIR SYSTEM - EPS (Expanded Polystyrene) and comfort liner align to maximize airflow
  • LIGHTWEIGHT ALUMINUM HARDWARE – helmet is constructed using super-strong, lightweight machined aluminum screws, rivets, and D-rings for superior strength and years of worry free use
  • OPTIONAL CARBON FIBER INTAKE VENT WING – can be added to the helmet for increased direction of airflow on the front vents

catalog_description:
The F2 Carbon represents race-inspired lightweight helmet technology for the masses. Based on the same platform as the Formula MX, the F2 Carbon shares many of the technological features as its predecessor, yet still carves out its own unique FLY Racing style and identity.

  • SNELL, DOT APPROVED FOR USA - other standards include: ECE and AS (Australian). Meets or exceeds the toughest safety standards on the market
  • COMPOSITE CONSTRUCTION SHELL – outer shell is constructed using state-of-the-art, aircraft grade woven carbon fiber and Kevlar® composite materials, which creates superior strength while remaining extremely light
  • DUAL DENSITY EPS LINER – two layers of EPS (Expanded Polystyrene), one softer one slightly harder, combine to provide more progressive impact absorption for different levels of impact
  • MULTI-PORT AIR INDUCTION COOLING SYSTEM – eleven (11) intake and four (4) exhaust vents create massive airflow to keep your head cool
  • TRI-VENT GOGGLE ANTI-FOG VENTS – three (3) air intake vents above goggle eye port draw air from goggle to help clear away fog
  • CUSTOM MOLDED RUBBER TRIM WITH NOSE GUARD - with its smooth lines the integrated nose guard helps keep pesky rocks away from your nose
  • QUICK RELEASE WASHABLE COMFORT LINER & CHEEK PADS – plush liner absorbs sweat, provides plenty of ventilation, and is easy to remove and clean with out “Quick Snap” system
  • FLOW THROUGH EPS AND COMFORT LINER AIR SYSTEM - EPS (Expanded Polystyrene) and comfort liner align to maximize airflow
  • LIGHTWEIGHT ALUMINUM HARDWARE – helmet is constructed using super-strong, lightweight machined aluminum screws, rivets, and D-rings for superior strength and years of worry free use
  • OPTIONAL CARBON FIBER INTAKE VENT WING – can be added to the helmet for increased direction of airflow on the front vents

• SNELL DOT APPROVED FOR USA - other standards include: ECE and AS (Australian). Meets or exceeds the toughest safety standards on the market
  • COMPOSITE CONSTRUCTION SHELL ndash outer shell is constructed using state-of-the-art aircraft grade woven carbon fiber and Kevlar reg composite materials which creates superior strength while remaining extremely light
  • DUAL DENSITY EPS LINER ndash two layers of EPS (Expanded Polystyrene) one softer one slightly harder combine to provide more progressive impact absorption for different levels of impact
  • MULTI-PORT AIR INDUCTION COOLING SYSTEM ndash eleven (11) intake and four (4) exhaust vents create massive airflow to keep your head cool
  • TRI-VENT GOGGLE ANTI-FOG VENTS ndash three (3) air intake vents above goggle eye port draw air from goggle to help clear away fog
  • CUSTOM MOLDED RUBBER TRIM WITH NOSE GUARD - with its smooth lines the integrated nose guard helps keep pesky rocks away from your nose
  • QUICK RELEASE WASHABLE COMFORT LINER amp CHEEK PADS ndash plush liner absorbs sweat provides plenty of ventilation and is easy to remove and clean with out ldquo Quick Snap rdquo system
  • FLOW THROUGH EPS AND COMFORT LINER AIR SYSTEM - EPS (Expanded Polystyrene) and comfort liner align to maximize airflow
  • LIGHTWEIGHT ALUMINUM HARDWARE ndash helmet is constructed using super-strong lightweight machined aluminum screws rivets and D-rings for superior strength and years of worry free use

description: F2 CARBON SNOW DUBSTEP HELMET BLACK/ORANGE 2X
catalog_description:
You've seen Fly Racing's elite athlete's such as Colten Moore and Heath Frisby dominate the winter games taking home multiple medals.  Racer's such as Tucker Hibbert, Ross Martin, and factory Yamaha taking snocross and cross country podiums and championships.  Backcountry experts Dan Adams and Geoff Kyle, hillclimbers like Russ Frisby, Erin Beukelman, the Sharp family, Tapio brothers, and many more, all dominating the snow wearing our F2 helmet.  Fly Racing now introduces our snow specific F2 Carbon helmet.

  • Snell M2010, DOT approved for USA.  Other safety standards include ECE and AS (Australian).  Meets or exceeds the toughest safety standards on the market.
  • ISR approved for any type of snowmobile competition
  • Visible snow specific graphic and design
  • Same shell and interior feautres as the current F2 Carbon helmet
  • Includes a cold weather plug kit to help block the cold weather
  • Features a custom molded F2 breath deflector to block flying debris

description: F2 CARBON SOLID HELMET MATTE BLACK 2X
catalog_description:
• SNELL DOT APPROVED FOR USA - other standards include: ECE and AS (Australian). Meets or exceeds the toughest safety standards on the market
  • COMPOSITE CONSTRUCTION SHELL ndash outer shell is constructed using state-of-the-art aircraft grade woven carbon fiber and Kevlar reg composite materials which creates superior strength while remaining extremely light
  • DUAL DENSITY EPS LINER ndash two layers of EPS (Expanded Polystyrene) one softer one slightly harder combine to provide more progressive impact absorption for different levels of impact
  • MULTI-PORT AIR INDUCTION COOLING SYSTEM ndash eleven (11) intake and four (4) exhaust vents create massive airflow to keep your head cool
  • TRI-VENT GOGGLE ANTI-FOG VENTS ndash three (3) air intake vents above goggle eye port draw air from goggle to help clear away fog
  • CUSTOM MOLDED RUBBER TRIM WITH NOSE GUARD - with its smooth lines the integrated nose guard helps keep pesky rocks away from your nose
  • QUICK RELEASE WASHABLE COMFORT LINER amp CHEEK PADS ndash plush liner absorbs sweat provides plenty of ventilation and is easy to remove and clean with out ldquo Quick Snap rdquo system
  • FLOW THROUGH EPS AND COMFORT LINER AIR SYSTEM - EPS (Expanded Polystyrene) and comfort liner align to maximize airflow
  • LIGHTWEIGHT ALUMINUM HARDWARE ndash helmet is constructed using super-strong lightweight machined aluminum screws rivets and D-rings for superior strength and years of worry free use

description: F2 CARBON SOLID HELMET MATTE BLACK 3X
catalog_description:
The F2 Carbon represents race-inspired lightweight helmet technology for the masses. Based on the same platform as the Formula MX, the F2 Carbon shares many of the technological features as its predecessor, yet still carves out its own unique FLY Racing style and identity.

  • SNELL, DOT APPROVED FOR USA - other standards include: ECE and AS (Australian). Meets or exceeds the toughest safety standards on the market
  • COMPOSITE CONSTRUCTION SHELL – outer shell is constructed using state-of-the-art, aircraft grade woven carbon fiber and Kevlar® composite materials, which creates superior strength while remaining extremely light
  • DUAL DENSITY EPS LINER – two layers of EPS (Expanded Polystyrene), one softer one slightly harder, combine to provide more progressive impact absorption for different levels of impact
  • MULTI-PORT AIR INDUCTION COOLING SYSTEM – eleven (11) intake and four (4) exhaust vents create massive airflow to keep your head cool
  • TRI-VENT GOGGLE ANTI-FOG VENTS – three (3) air intake vents above goggle eye port draw air from goggle to help clear away fog
  • CUSTOM MOLDED RUBBER TRIM WITH NOSE GUARD - with its smooth lines the integrated nose guard helps keep pesky rocks away from your nose
  • QUICK RELEASE WASHABLE COMFORT LINER & CHEEK PADS – plush liner absorbs sweat, provides plenty of ventilation, and is easy to remove and clean with out “Quick Snap” system
  • FLOW THROUGH EPS AND COMFORT LINER AIR SYSTEM - EPS (Expanded Polystyrene) and comfort liner align to maximize airflow
  • LIGHTWEIGHT ALUMINUM HARDWARE – helmet is constructed using super-strong, lightweight machined aluminum screws, rivets, and D-rings for superior strength and years of worry free use
  • OPTIONAL CARBON FIBER INTAKE VENT WING – can be added to the helmet for increased direction of airflow on the front vents

description: KINETIC BLOCK OUT HELMET WHITE/RED YM
catalog_description:
Price should never dictate style, so we created the Kinetic helmet to be fashion-forward without spending a fortune. And like all FLY helmets, the Kinetic is created with the same attention-to-detail, focus on safety, and design bravado as our other helmets. With the Kinetic, there’s no need to sacrifice personal style for price.

  • DOT APPROVED FOR USA
  • POLY ALLOY SHELL - combination of high strength poly materials create a durable light weight shell
  • DUAL DENSITY EPS LINER – two layers of EPS (Expanded Polystyrene), one softer one slightly harder, combine to provide more progressive impact absorption
  • REMOVABLE LINER & CHEEK PADS - keep you looking clean, help extend the life of your helmet and is easy to use with our “Quick Snap” system
  • HIGH VOLUME VENTS – ten (10) massive vents aligned with EPS (Expanded Polystyrene) channels flow a huge volume of air through the helmet keeping you cooled. Large exhaust vents eliminate heat that builds up
  • HI-FLOW MOUTHPIECE - designed with a cool style and plenty of air flow
  • Optional breath guard available for cold weather P/N 73-4810

groups.51779: FLY KINETIC PRO COLD WEATHER HELMETS
FLY KINETIC PRO COLD WEATHER HELMETS
FLY KINETIC PRO COLD WEATHER HELMETS

catalog_description:
Fly Racing's Kinetic Pro Cold Weather helmets are the perfect choice for an all season helmet.  This economically priced helmet includes a custom graphic and removable breath guard.  Take it out for warm days, put it in for cold days! 

  • DOT and ECE approved for USA
  • Poly Alloy shell is a combination of high strength poly materials creating a durable lightweight shell
  • Dual density EPS liner has two layers of expanded polystyrene, one softer and one slightly harder, combined to provide more progressive impact absorption
  • Quick snap removable liner and cheek pads for drying out after a long day in the snow
  • Aluminum visor hardware helps make the Aurora even lighter
  • Intake and exhaust vents to help maintain a constant temperature and eliminate excess sweat causing heat
  • Adjustable breath deflector included to aid in blocking your face from flying debris and the elements

catalog_description:
• Snell DOT Approved For USA ndash other standards include: ECE and AS (Australian). Meets or exceeds the toughest safety standards on the market
  • Composite Shell Construction ndash outer shell is constructed using state-of-the-art aircraft grade woven carbon fiber and Kevlar reg composite materials which creates superior strength while remaining extremely light
  • Dual Density EPS Liner ndash two layers of EPS (Expanded Polystyrene) one softer one slightly harder combine to provide more progressive impact absorption for different levels of impact
  • Multi-port Air Induction Cooling System ndash eleven (11) intake and four (4) exhaust vents create massive airflow to keep your head cool. So cool that we include an air vent plug kit to keep you warm and cozy when riding in cold weather
  • Tri-vent Goggle Anti-fog Vents ndash three (3) air intake vents above goggle eye port draw air from goggle to help clear away fog
  • Flow Through EPS And Comfort Liner Air System ndash EPS (Expanded Polystyrene) and comfort liner align to maximize airflow
  • Quick Release Washable Coolmax reg Comfort Liner and Cheek Pads ndash ultra plush liner absorbs sweat is perforated to provide plenty of ventilation and easy to remove and clean with our ldquo Quick Snap rdquo system
  • Titanium Hardware ndash helmet is constructed using super-strong ultra-lightweight machined titanium screws rivets and D-rings for superior strength and years of worry free use
  • Premium Helmet Bag And Extra Visor ndash we include a stylish helmet bag with plenty of storage and padding to protect your investment and an extra visor with each helmet

description: F2 CARBON FASTBACK HELMET ORANGE/BLACK/WHITE X
catalog_description:
The F2 Carbon represents race-inspired lightweight helmet technology for the masses. Based on the same platform as the Formula MX, the F2 Carbon shares many of the technological features as its predecessor, yet still carves out its own unique FLY Racing style and identity.

  • SNELL, DOT APPROVED FOR USA - other standards include: ECE and AS (Australian). Meets or exceeds the toughest safety standards on the market
  • COMPOSITE CONSTRUCTION SHELL – outer shell is constructed using state-of-the-art, aircraft grade woven carbon fiber and Kevlar® composite materials, which creates superior strength while remaining extremely light
  • DUAL DENSITY EPS LINER – two layers of EPS (Expanded Polystyrene), one softer one slightly harder, combine to provide more progressive impact absorption for different levels of impact
  • MULTI-PORT AIR INDUCTION COOLING SYSTEM – eleven (11) intake and four (4) exhaust vents create massive airflow to keep your head cool
  • TRI-VENT GOGGLE ANTI-FOG VENTS – three (3) air intake vents above goggle eye port draw air from goggle to help clear away fog
  • CUSTOM MOLDED RUBBER TRIM WITH NOSE GUARD - with its smooth lines the integrated nose guard helps keep pesky rocks away from your nose
  • QUICK RELEASE WASHABLE COMFORT LINER & CHEEK PADS – plush liner absorbs sweat, provides plenty of ventilation, and is easy to remove and clean with out “Quick Snap” system
  • FLOW THROUGH EPS AND COMFORT LINER AIR SYSTEM - EPS (Expanded Polystyrene) and comfort liner align to maximize airflow
  • LIGHTWEIGHT ALUMINUM HARDWARE – helmet is constructed using super-strong, lightweight machined aluminum screws, rivets, and D-rings for superior strength and years of worry free use
  • OPTIONAL CARBON FIBER INTAKE VENT WING – can be added to the helmet for increased direction of airflow on the front vents

description: F2 CARBON ACETYLENE HELMET WHITE/RED XS
catalog_description:
The F2 Carbon represents race-inspired lightweight helmet technology for the masses. Based on the same platform as the Formula MX, the F2 Carbon shares many of the technological features as its predecessor, yet still carves out its own unique FLY Racing style and identity.

  • SNELL, DOT APPROVED FOR USA - other standards include: ECE and AS (Australian). Meets or exceeds the toughest safety standards on the market
  • COMPOSITE CONSTRUCTION SHELL – outer shell is constructed using state-of-the-art, aircraft grade woven carbon fiber and Kevlar® composite materials, which creates superior strength while remaining extremely light
  • DUAL DENSITY EPS LINER – two layers of EPS (Expanded Polystyrene), one softer one slightly harder, combine to provide more progressive impact absorption for different levels of impact
  • MULTI-PORT AIR INDUCTION COOLING SYSTEM – eleven (11) intake and four (4) exhaust vents create massive airflow to keep your head cool
  • TRI-VENT GOGGLE ANTI-FOG VENTS – three (3) air intake vents above goggle eye port draw air from goggle to help clear away fog
  • CUSTOM MOLDED RUBBER TRIM WITH NOSE GUARD - with its smooth lines the integrated nose guard helps keep pesky rocks away from your nose
  • QUICK RELEASE WASHABLE COMFORT LINER & CHEEK PADS – plush liner absorbs sweat, provides plenty of ventilation, and is easy to remove and clean with out “Quick Snap” system
  • FLOW THROUGH EPS AND COMFORT LINER AIR SYSTEM - EPS (Expanded Polystyrene) and comfort liner align to maximize airflow
  • LIGHTWEIGHT ALUMINUM HARDWARE – helmet is constructed using super-strong, lightweight machined aluminum screws, rivets, and D-rings for superior strength and years of worry free use
  • OPTIONAL CARBON FIBER INTAKE VENT WING – can be added to the helmet for increased direction of airflow on the front vents
